2020-07-26 05: 03: 17 Source: Beijing Youth Daily Author: Wang Sisuo Responsibility Editor: Wang Sisuo
Capital's natural ecology continues to attract wildlife cities to "settle"
Beijing wildlife has reached more than 500 species.
Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the Municipal Landscaping Bureau that in recent years, with the continuous improvement of the natural ecological environment of the capital, the types and quantities of wild animals have also continued to increase.
At present, terrestrial vertebrate wildlife that inhabits Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including national-level protected animals such as brown horse chickens and black storks, as well as second-level protected animals such as wildebeests, swans, gray cranes, and mandarins.
Whether it is planting a city forest in the second ring, or a small wetland embedded in the building, it not only brings the wild fun of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attracts wildlife to "settle" in the city.
In the summer season, it is a vibrant nature in the Songshan National Nature Reserve in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District.
A raccoon played leisurely by the mountain stream, and on the side, the two badgers hit each other.
Looking back, a wild boar can't help but "sting" his body, "stinging" is rubbing the bark. Hu Qiaoli, director of the Matsuyama National Nature Reserve Management Office, said that as of the end of 2019, in this green sea with a total area of more than 6200 hectares, there are 178 species of wild animals, including national-level protection of animal vaults and national secondary protection of animal-level protected spoond chickens and antelopes.
"In Matsuyama, wild animals are the real 'master', and our staff can only be regarded as the 'bodyguard' of people's bodies at best."
Hu said that in order to understand the situation of wildlife in the protected area on the ground, more than 30 professional rangers are patrolling along the 16 carefully formulated protection routes, and there will be a trip to "turn the circle" every month, and spend a whole day walking through the entire protected area.
"In the inspection, not only to check the record of biodiversity, but also to check the installation of artificial nests, to rescue injured wildlife, the installation of field infrared cameras and so on."
The Songshan National Nature Reserve has now installed more than 200 infrared cameras to record the living conditions of the wildlife in the forest.
Hu Qioli introduced that with the continuous enrichment of the biodiversity of the protected area in recent years, more and more wild animals appear in the lens, leopard cats, raccoon and pig badgers have become "resident guests", and the "out of the film" of the national secondary protected animal antelope is also getting higher and higher.
Zhang Zhiming, director of the Wildlife and Wetland Protection Department of the Beijing Municipal Landscaping Bureau, said that Beijing's terrestrial spine wildlife has increased from 461 species in 1994 to more than 500 now, and the number of wildlife species and number in Beijing has continued to increase in recent years.
The figure of wildlife in the city is more and more common, which is closely related to the continuous upgrading of the urban greening of the capital city in recent
In particular, the construction of a new round of million-acre afforestation began in 2018, proposing to reshape the urban ecological environment, enhance the ecological function of forest land green space, and highlight the concept of "near nature".
Planning and strive to interact with the surrounding green space, so that wildlife can "walk around relatives and friends", and the trees planted are also the honey source and food plants that animals love.
Black land "plants" out of agricultural modernization - Xinhua Network
Xinhua News Agency Harbin July 26th Topic: Black Land "plants" Out of Agricultural Modernization
In midsummer, two spraying medication aircraft passed through the million-acre high-yield demonstration field of the second operating station of the fifth management area of Friendship Farm, forming two white lines, and the "first game in the world" in the green fields was particularly eye-catching.
The station director, pon., said that this aircraft can spray more than 6000 acres of arable land a day, which is about eight times the efficiency of drones, and is hundreds of times that of artificial.
This farm is located in the country's first grain-producing province of Heilongjiang Friendship County, from the past "swipe" rice cutting sound to the current "rumble" motor sound, Chinese traditional farming and farms in this black soil belt to achieve metamorphosis.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in modern agricultural production on Friendship Farms.
On the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural investment, and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the level of standardized operation between agricultural machinery fields.
In this year's rice production, the farm has expanded the area of the satellite navigation unmanned transplant technology from 3000 acres last year to 30000 acres.
This technology makes seedlings more uniform, which can maximize the use of sunlight and arable land resources, and save 16 yuan of labor costs per acre.
The farm tries new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total amount of farm machinery currently has 4.9 million units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate of the field reaches 99.8%.
Agricultural machine operations achieve GPS satellite navigation 100%, dry field precision seeding 100%, dry field macar operation 100%.
"Green agriculture, smart agriculture, and digital agriculture are the pathfinding directions of agricultural modernization."
Friendship Farmer Director Liu Hualian said.
The key to the modernization of agriculture is scientific and technological progress.
In recent years, Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation, represented by the farm, has played a demonstration and leading role in modern large-scale agricultural "carrier", and initially established a modern agricultural industry system dominated by large-scale cultivation, standardized production, and industrialization management.
On the outskirts of Friendship County, there is a farmhouse with an area of 35 million square meters.
More than 140 (pieces) of agricultural machinery introduced and used in Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation over the years have been exhibited here.
These agricultural machinery and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
