Comprehensive news: U.S. unilateralism undermines international public opinion on bilateral relations and supports China's counter-U.S.-Xinhua
On the morning of July 24th, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the U.S. Embassy in China that it decided to revoke the establishment and operation of the U.S. Consulate General in Chengdu and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to stop all operations and activities of the Consulate General in Chengdu.
International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious problems in the relations between China and the United States, and it is legitimate and necessary for China to respond to the unreasonable provocations of the US and take countermeasures.
Andrés Bolks, director of the China Research Center of the Institute of International Studies at the University of Chile, said that the unilateral measures of the United States have undermined the bridge of understanding between the two peoples and caused the two major countries to face a crisis.
China has informed the United States that the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures of the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Justo, a professor at the Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Arab-Chinese Studies Center, believes that the above-mentioned decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure against the United States' previous provocations, and is not aimed at ordinary Americans.
The United States has tried to divert the attention of the American people by pressuring China to cover up its lack of response to the coronavirus outbreak.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Center for Asian Innovation Studies, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic gesture of the United States has caused serious problems in the relations between China and the United States, and the relationship between the two countries faces severe challenges.
China's notification to the United States that the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure and in line with diplomatic practice, which reflects both China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also reflects the rational and beneficial nature of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian current affairs commentator Francis Semwenza said that China's decision was a legitimate and necessary response to the provocation of the United States.
To return to normal China-US relations, the US side should take the initiative to improve its relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve a win-win situation with China economically and politically and how it can benefit the two peoples and the international community as a whole.
Ali Yusuf, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab-Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures that China is forced to take is a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the US side, conforms to international law and the basic norms of international relations, and is also in line with diplomatic practice.
Earlier, the United States demanded the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston a serious violation of international law and the basic norms of international relations.
It is hoped that the US side will rescind its previous decision and create the necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
An editorial in Singapore's United Morning Post said the U.S.'s larger strategic intention was to contain China and prevent China from continuing its rise.
In the face of the US, although China is very reluctant to see China-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has to take countermeasures.
