The "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the National Information Center Sharing Economic Research Center recently shows that the impact of the epidemic, in the first five months of 2020, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market decreased by 72.1% year-on-year.
However, the shared accommodation market has warmed since March, and the market turnover, order volume and reception have gradually recovered.
The report shows that the volume of shared accommodation market volume has dropped significantly, on the one hand, due to the sharp decline in demand for travel accommodation under the prevention and control of the epidemic, the sharp reduction in the order volume, the total number of orders in the first five months fell by 65% year-on-year, and the number of receptions decreased by 63% year-on-year. On the other hand, the weak demand has also led to a more obvious decline in night prices, and the average night price has declined by 16% year-on-year in the previous five months.
However, the market turnover in March, April and May increased by 78%, 199% and 35% respectively; the number of orders increased by 141 percent, 152% and 50% respectively; the number of receptions increased by 81%, 112% and 28% respectively.
The report pointed out that the development of shared accommodation industry has been optimistic for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
