Mr. Wen immediately took Xiaowen to the hospital for treatment and was diagnosed with an external injury.
Mr. Wen believes that the facilities of the school stadium do not meet the relevant safety regulations and do not effectively manage the team and related facilities.
The negligence of the school led to the above-mentioned events, resulting in great suffering caused by Xiaowen's physical and mental suffering, and at the same time brought great pain to his family, which should bear legal responsibility for this school.
In this regard, the school argued that the school has set up a protective net in the playground, and posted management regulations, training notices, told the playground to keep a safe distance from the training site and remind itself of its own safety, the plaintiff can not prove that the school "has not fulfilled the safety and security obligations, so it does not agree to compensation."
After the trial, the court held that the venue involved in the incident was a free venue for the public, and although the school had a security obligation for the management of the playground, it was necessary to meet the general obligation of care.
At the time of the incident, the school set up a protective net in the playground, and has fulfilled the appropriate safety and security obligations, and Chen also compensated Xiaowen for medical expenses, transportation expenses and other losses of more than two thousand yuan in accordance with the compensation agreement reached.
Afterwards, Xiaowen's parents once again advocated for school compensation, and there was no basis for law, and the court ruled to dismiss all the plaintiff's application.
After the sentence, neither party appealed, and the judgment has now entered into force.
According to article 37 of China's tort liability law, the school, as the administrator of a public place, has the obligation of safety and security; in the case of the damage caused by the actions of the third party, the third party bears the responsibility for tort or tort, and the public place manager who fails to fulfill the safety and security obligation shall bear the corresponding supplementary liability.
The judge said that since as the administrator of a public place, it is most likely to understand the actual situation of the entire place, foresee the potential danger and damage, so that it is most likely that the necessary measures are necessary to prevent the extent of the damage from occurring or mitigating the extent of the damage, and to avoid and mitigate the minimum cost of damage, so the law stipulates that it shall bear the corresponding guarantee obligation for social activities.
In this case, the school's security obligations should be commensurate with the social activities carried out in the social activities that are not specific to the public in the playground free of charge, mainly to take basic security measures and the obligation to inform the risk of concealment.
In judicial practice, it is not appropriate to have a high security obligation for the management of public places.
If the school has taken the protective net and fulfills the obligation of notification, it can be determined that the school is not at fault and should not bear legal responsibility.
In addition, for third-party infringement, even if the administrator of a public place such as the school fails to fulfill the safety and security obligations, its liability is also a supplement to the damages. According to the latest promulgation of the Civil Code, after the supercharger bears the supplementary responsibility, it can also recover from the third party.
Therefore, in such accidents, the victim should not expand the scope of the claim after receiving compensation from the direct infringer.
