Before filling in the voluntary report, I understand what is a professional grade difference - China New Network
2020-07-27 02: 22: 36 Source: Chongqing Morning News Author: Yu Xiao Responsibility Editor: Yu Xiao
Before filling in the voluntary report, you can understand what is a professional grade difference.
Every year, students or parents do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary report, and then affect the voluntary filing.
This year, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, Beijing University of Chemical Technology, five universities jointly issued the 2020 admissions policy and eliminated the professional grade difference.
What does professional grade difference mean, and what is the significance of volunteering?
There are three ways of professional distribution rules.
Experts remind that before filling in the volunteer, we must study the admissions of the school's admissions charter to understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the proportion of transfer, professional distribution rules and so on.
The professional allocation rules, refers to the college after the transfer, for professional admissions mainly have professional priority, score priority, professional grade difference of three ways.
Which method of use by colleges and universities will be clear in the Admissions Charter.
But there are some colleges and universities admission principles that are the total priority, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, the admission of candidates in accordance with the total score line, when the score does not reach the first professional volunteer admission score line, it depends on whether the second professional volunteer admission score line, so until the admission to the last professional volunteer, there is no grade difference between professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" is that when the college arranges candidates for majors, according to one or more of the values published in the admissions charter, to determine the admission of different professional volunteer candidates, this score is "professional grade difference."
That is, the difference in the scores of the college in the admission of candidates for the first professional and non-first professional volunteer, and the difference in the grade difference of each major volunteer, such as 3 points, 2 points, and 1 points.
For example.
Assume that students Xiaoming applied for the A university, the examination of 560 points, its professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce, A university professional admission to the implementation of professional grade difference, grade difference is divided into two points, 1 points, 1 points, 0 points.
In the professional allocation, if Xiaoming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and has a planned balance, then Xiao Ming is admitted to "computer science" major; if the computer is not accepted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, according to the score of 558 points and the first professional volunteer examination of candidates for "international trade" sort, determine whether it meets the professional admission conditions; if it is still not satisfied, the third professional volunteer "automated"; if it is still can not meet the fourth major admission;Volunteer, will no longer be reduced, and so on.
Different college professional grade differential settings
With the popularity of parallel volunteers, many colleges and universities have now canceled the professional grade difference, but some colleges and universities have retained this method this method this year, from the "Admissions Charter" published by various schools, this year, more than two decades of universities have set up professional grade differentials.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight School, etc.
In these colleges and universities, the professional grade differential set by each university is different.
Some colleges and universities have grade differentials in each major, such as Ningxia University, the file has been submitted to the school candidates, according to the order of candidates to fill in the professional volunteer order in order of regression by score admission.
Some universities have different professional grade differentials between different majors.
For example, at Jimei University, the total score of the professional volunteer grade is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and the other professional volunteer level is three points, and the other professional volunteer does not set a grade difference, which is regarded as a parallel volunteer, and the professional volunteer ratio between the professional and the adjustment of the professional level is one.
When filling in the volunteer, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school, to see if there is a professional grade difference, the form of difference is, in full consideration of the score at the same time, but also reasonable analysis of the selected schools and majors, if the admissions regulations clearly take the score difference mode of admission, candidates in the choice of majors, pay attention to the gradient between the majors, improve the admission probability.
